message.content: We begin by moving all the terms to the left-hand side to obtain $x^2 + 5x - 6 < 0$. This inequality factors as $(x-1)(x+6) < 0$. Setting both factors equal to zero shows that $x=1$ and $x=-6$ are critical values.  Testing a number in each of the intervals defined by these critical values shows that $x^2+5x-6 <0$ when $-6 < x < 1$.  This interval can be expressed in interval notation as $\boxed{(-6,1)}$.
